Please answer the below core-java Questions:

What is programing language?
A. A programming language is a special language programmers use to develop software programs, scripts, or other sets of
    instructions for computers to execute.
What jdk contains or composed of and define each components?
A. It includes the Java Runtime Environment (JRE), an interpreter/loader(java), a compiler (javac), an archiver(jar),a
     documentation generator (javadoc) and other tools needed in Java development.
What is IDE?
A. An IDE is a software application which enables users to more easily write and debug Java programs.
What are the IDEs available in the market to support java? Eclipse, NetBeans, IntelliJ, BlueJ
Explain the entire java life cycle. The code is written in a text editor, converted into a .java source file,
    goes through a Java compiler and turned into Bytecode, goes through the JVM and than into the Operating System.
what is class? A class are templates that are used to create objects, and to define object data types and methods.
What is object? Objects are states and behaviors.
What is the entry point of an application? The Main Method.
Why main is static? The keyword static allows main to be called without having to instantiate a particular instance of
    the class.
Which class is the superclass of all classes? The Object class.
What is difference between path and classpath variables? Path is an environment variable which is used by the operating
    system to find the executables. Classpath is an environment variable which is used by the Java compiler to find the
    path.
What is the difference between an Interface and Abstract class? An interface can mostly declare methods, it can implement
    methods if it is static. A method in Abstract class can only declare, methods without abstract has to implement.

Can you make an Object from an Interface and Abstract class ? if not how do you use it ? No, you would use the Interface
    or Abstract class by extending it or implementing it through a concrete class.
what is Access Specifier? Access Specifiers specifies accessbibility of a data member, method, constructor or class.
What is OOP ? Define each feature of java OOP. OOP is Object Oriented Programming,
Inheritance: When one object acquires all the properties and behaviors of a parent object.
Polymorphism: One task is performed by different ways. Also method overloading and method overriding.
Abstraction: Hiding internal details and showing functionality.
Encapsulation: Binding code and data together into a single unit.
What is Java Package and which package is imported by default? A package is a mechanism to encapsulate a group of classes.
    Java.lang package is imported by default.
What is API? Name list of API that you have used so far. An API is a Application Programming Interface. Java.util.Scanner,
    java.io.BufferedReader, java.util.ArrayList,
Does java support multiple inheritance, explain why or why not? No, not through class. To reduce the complexity and
    simplify the language.
What is method overloading and when it happens? Method Overloading happens when a class has multiple methods with the
    same name but different parameters.
Explain exceptions in java and how to handle it. An exception is an abnormal condition. We use Exception Handling which
    is a mechanism to handle runtime errors such as ClassNotFoundException, IOException, SQLException, RemoteExeption, etc
